---
import DocLayout from "../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout title="File formats">
  <h1>Supported file formats</h1>
  <p>
    All formats use the <code>{`Name.<sourceLocale>.<ext>`}</code> naming convention.
    The action reads the source file, translates the values, and writes a sibling
    file per target locale (e.g. <code>Greetings.fr.resx</code>).
  </p>

  <h2>.resx (.NET resource)</h2>
  <p>
    XML-based .NET resource files. Translates the inner text of each
    <code>&lt;data&gt;&lt;value&gt;</code> node, preserving comments and
    metadata.
  </p>

  <h2>.xliff (XLIFF 2.0)</h2>
  <p>
    OASIS XLIFF 2.0 documents. Translates each <code>&lt;source&gt;</code>
    and writes the result into the corresponding <code>&lt;target&gt;</code>,
    setting <code>trgLang</code> for the locale.
  </p>

  <h2>.po (gettext)</h2>
  <p>
    GNU gettext Portable Object files. Translates each <code>msgid</code> /
    <code>msgid_plural</code> into <code>msgstr</code> / <code>msgstr[n]</code>
    forms.
  </p>

  <h2>.json</h2>
  <p>
    Arbitrary JSON files. Nested objects are flattened with the
    <code>[--]</code> delimiter for translation, then re-nested on output.
    Dotted keys (e.g. <code>"unit.dotted.key"</code>) are preserved verbatim.
  </p>

  <h2>.ini / .restext</h2>
  <p>
    Simple <code>key=value</code> files (Win32-style INI, MUI <code>.restext</code>,
    or any flat config). Section headers and comments are preserved.
  </p>

  <h2>Round-trip guarantees</h2>
  <p>
    The test suite verifies byte-for-byte round-tripping for representative
    fixtures of every format. If a format quirk breaks round-tripping in
    your codebase, please open an issue with a minimal sample.
  </p>
</DocLayout>
